sql:
SELECT sample_id
FROM samples
ORDER BY collection_date ASC, sample_id ASC;

external_knowledge:
RI (Refractive Index) is a measure of how much a light beam bends as it passes through a medium, such as a sample; 
The top-ranked samples are those with the highest RI values within each site;
Sample types include soil and rock; 
Operators are individuals or organizations responsible for collecting the samples;
Geological formations refer to the underlying structure of the Earth's crust in the sample area;
Latitude and longitude specify the geographical location of the sample sites.

- Analysis results refer to the chemical composition of the samples (RI, NA, MG, AL, SI, KA, CA, BA, FE); 
- Sample quality can be 'good' or 'poor', indicating the condition of the sample; 
- Access type can be 'view' or 'download', indicating how users interacted with the samples; 
- Sample status can be 'collected', 'under analysis', or 'completed', indicating the processing stage of the samples.
